'HEX DUMP' EXTENDS THE FUNCTIONALITYOF THE MONITOR. 'BLOAD HEX DUMP' TOINSTALL THE PATCH (DO NOT BRUN IT).THEN; IN THE MONITOR; SPECIFY ANADDRESSRANGE THE WAY YOU NORMALLYWOULD FOR AHEX DUMP; BUT PRESS CTRL-Y BEFOREHITTING RETURN. THE HEX DUMP WILLCONTAIN SIXTEEN BYTES PER LINE; WITHTHE ASCII EQUIVALENTS. SIXTEEN BYTESPER LINE IS IDEAL FOR AN 80-COLUMNSCREEN OR PRINTER. FOR 40-COLUMNS;POKE 975;8 (OR TYPE '3CF:8' FROM THEMONITOR) FIRST; TO SPECIFY EIGHTBYTES PER LINE.EXAMPLE USE: ]CALL -151 *38C.3CF<CTRL-Y>